' `Result` is a runtime-only type: a call's outcome is auto-unwrapped on
' success or auto-propagated (or caught by an inline `TRAP`) on failure. A user
' can never scrutinize the implicit `Result` with `MATCH`, so `CASE Ok` and
' `CASE Error` are rejected with TYPE_RESULT_NOT_MATCHABLE.
FUNC parse(value AS Integer) AS Integer
  IF value < 0 THEN FAIL error(900, "negative")
  RETURN value
END FUNC

FUNC main AS Integer
  MATCH parse(5)
    CASE Ok(value)
      RETURN value
    CASE Error(err)
      RETURN err.code
  END MATCH
END FUNC
